    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-10-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-10-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="10"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d10">
                <head>EXHIBIT E.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Francisco</hi>
                        </placeName>,<date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-10-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 31, 1891</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I hereby agree with J. and W. R. Wing to go master of the bark <hi rend="italic"
                        >Cape Horn Pigeon</hi> on her next contemplated season, to sail from this
                    port by Dec. 1st, 1891, to go east and return as above and join said bark at
                    this port, the said Wings to pay one-half (½) round trip ticket to Boston and
                    back to this port, the other half to be charged to me. Compensation to be the
                    (1/12) lay in net proceeds of voyage.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thomas Scullun.</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>Approved:<lb/>
                    <signed>J.</signed> and <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. R. Wing.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>I hereby certify that the above is a true and exact copy of the original
                        contract, letter for letter and figure for figure.</p>
                    <closer>[<hi rend="smallcaps">seal.</hi>] <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. F. Caswell</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Notary
                                Public.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
